cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about multilingual neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses language embeddings, which are learned through a neural network, indicating that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a clustering method to group languages, which involves making decisions based on data, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions using a universal neural machine translation model, which is a type of neural network, indicating that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of multilingual NMT in computer vision, indicating that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
